      "content": "that makes sense. so basically you need to get the water out of the way first. since it's such a complex series of steps, is there any way to control the outcome more precisely, or is it just kind of a chaotic mess once it starts? also is there any specific way the flavor profile shifts if you stay at the lower end of that temperature range vs going higher?",
