      "content": "You've hit on a key point, and it's much more controlled than a chaotic mess, though it certainly has its own flavor profile quirks! Controlling the outcome is all about managing time and temperature, which is where the culinary art comes in.\n\nIf you stay at the lower end of the effective range (say, closer to 285°F/140°C), you'll get more gentle, nutty, and sweet-smelling compounds. If you push it higher, say past 325°F (160°C) and into the deep brown zone, you start generating more intense, roasted, and sometimes slightly bitter notes. It's a gradient, not a switch!",
